<p>I have a Serivce class, a reciever class with BroadcastReceiver and a MainActivitiy class. I am trying to send data from BroadcastReceiver to MainActivity while service is running. I need that data in MainActivity when receiver class do his task. I have a method but android does not acces to do this.</p>  <pre><code>                            //TRYING TO SEND DATA                              Intent s = new Intent();                             s.setClass(MyReceiver.this, MainActivity.class);                             s.putExtra("dn", words[1]);                             startActivity(s); </code></pre>  <p>I came from <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2616859/how-do-i-pass-data-from-a-broadcastreceiver-through-to-an-activity-being-started">BroadcastReceiver Pass Data</a></p>  <p>But I could not use this solution.</p>  <p>Edit:Now I have a solution.</p>  <p>In reciever.java:</p>  <pre><code>Intent intent2open = new Intent(arg0, MainActivity.class); intent2open.addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK); intent2open.addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_SINGLE_TOP); String name = "KEY"; String value = words[1]; intent2open.putExtra(name, value); arg0.startActivity(intent2open); Toast.makeText(arg0, words[1], Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show(); </code></pre>  <p>And MainActivity.java:</p>  <pre><code> @Override protected void onNewIntent(Intent intent) {     Log.d("YourActivity", "onNewIntent is called!");      string1 = intent.getStringExtra("KEY");      super.onNewIntent(intent);  } </code></pre>